  "prompt": "What are the best ways to cook winkles?",
  "response": "Winkles, a type of small marine snail, are a delicacy in some regions and can be prepared in several delicious ways. Here are some of the best methods to cook winkles:\n\n1. **Boiling**: \n   - **Steps**: Start by rinsing the winkles in cold water to remove any sand. Bring a pot of salted water to a boil, then add the winkles. Boil for about 5-10 minutes until they start to curl up. \n   - **Serving**: Drain and serve them hot, possibly with melted butter or a garlic dip.\n\n2. **Steaming**: \n   - **Steps**: Place winkles in a steamer basket over boiling water. Steam for about 5-7 minutes or until cooked through.\n   - **Serving**: They can be served plain, with a squeeze of lemon, or accompanied by dipping sauces.\n\n3. **Garlic Butter**:\n   - **Steps**: Boil or steam the winkles as described above. In a separate pan, melt butter and saut\u00e9 minced garlic. Toss the cooked winkles in the garlic butter for a flavorful finish.\n   - **Serving**: Serve hot, garnished with parsley or lemon zest.\n\n4. **Pasta**: \n   - Utilize winkles as a protein in pasta dishes. After boiling or steaming, add them to pasta with olive oil, garlic, chili flakes, and fresh herbs.\n   - **Serving**: This can be served with a sprinkle of grated cheese.\n\n5. **Seafood Salad**:\n   - After boiling the winkles, allow them to cool and combine them with other seafood, fresh vegetables, and a light dressing for a refreshing salad.\n   - **Serving**: Garnish with herbs like dill or parsley.\n\n6. **Alcohol Pairing**: \n   - Winkling can also be enjoyed simply with a dipping sauce or on their own, often paired with a glass of white wine or beer.\n\nWhen preparing winkles, remember to ensure they are sourced from clean waters to avoid any food safety issues. Enjoy your cooking!",
